<!doctype html>

<head>
  <title>Help</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css"
    integrity="sha384-Gn5384xqQ1aoWXA+058RXPxPg6fy4IWvTNh0E263XmFcJlSAwiGgFAW/dAiS6JXm" crossorigin="anonymous">
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/style.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.7.1/css/all.css"
    integrity="sha384-fnmOCqbTlWIlj8LyTjo7mOUStjsKC4pOpQbqyi7RrhN7udi9RwhKkMHpvLbHG9Sr" crossorigin="anonymous">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.7.2/css/all.css" integrity="sha384-fnmOCqbTlWIlj8LyTjo7mOUStjsKC4pOpQbqyi7RrhN7udi9RwhKkMHpvLbHG9Sr" crossorigin="anonymous">
</head>

<body>
  {{> navbar showBackBtn="false"}}

  <div class="container">

    <div>
      <button class="collapsible">Q: What is CMPLTR? <i class="fas fa-caret-down"></i></button>
      <div class="content">
      <p>CMPLTR, short for Completer, is a progress routine manager that notifies you when to do your task and rewards
        you for each consecutive day completed. After completing your task for the day, you record it on the app, and it
        rewards you with visual and auditory positive feedback.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    </hr>

    <div>
      <button class="collapsible">Q: How do I create a routine? <i class="fas fa-caret-down"></i></button>
      <div class="content">
      <p>Click on the "Create Routine" button where you can create and customize your routine based on the total amount of days you wish to complete,
        when you want to be notified, and optionally what goals you wish to achieve, as well as, rewards you wish to recieve upon completing the routine and goals.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    </hr>

    <div>
      <button class="collapsible">Q: How do I check my current routine? <i class="fas fa-caret-down"></i></button>
      <div class="content">
      <p>Click on the "Current Routines" button where you will be able to see all the routines that are currently active. You can then click on one to see more details of that routine,
         in addition to recording your completed days.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    </hr>

    <div>
      <button class="collapsible">Q: Where can I see the old routines that I have completed? <i class="fas fa-caret-down"></i></button>
      <div class="content">
      <p>Click on the "Previous Routines" button where you be able to see all archived routines. You can then click on one to see more details of that routine. 
        You cannot edit them, but you can view them.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    </hr>

    <div>
      <button class="collapsible">Q: Can I see other user's activity and progress? <i class="fas fa-caret-down"></i></button>
      <div class="content">
      <p>Click on the "See Community Feed" to see a ongoing list of users and their progression in their routines.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    </hr>

    <div>
      <button class="collapsible">Q: What do the circles on Current and Previous Routine mean? <i class="fas fa-caret-down"></i></button>
      <div class="content">
      <p>The circles represent each day that is to be completed for the routine. After doing the task for the specified
        day, you press the circle, it lights up, gives you a positive message, and plays a tone.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    </hr>

    <div>
      <button class="collapsible">Q: How do I record a completed day for a routine? <i class="fas fa-caret-down"></i></button>
      <div class="content">
      <p>Go to the current routine that corresponds to the activity you are recording for and click on the circle with the completion date. </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="divider">
    </hr>

    <div>
      <button class="collapsible">Q: What happens when you finish a routine? <i class="fas fa-caret-down"></i></button>
      <div class="content">
      <p>Click on the "Mark Completed" button at the bottom of routine, and it will ask whether you completed the intended goals. Afterwards, your routine
        will be archived in the previous routines page, where you can view it at any time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
  var coll = document.getElementsByClassName("collapsible");
  var i;

  for (i = 0; i < coll.length; i++) {
    coll[i].addEventListener("click", function() {
      this.classList.toggle("active");
      var content = this.nextElementSibling;
      if (content.style.display === "block") {
        content.style.display = "none";
      } else {
        content.style.display = "block";
      }
    });
  }
  </script>

  <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.3.1.slim.min.js"
    integrity="sha384-q8i/X+965DzO0rT7abK41JStQIAqVgRVzpbzo5smXKp4YfRvH+8abtTE1Pi6jizo"
    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/popper.js/1.14.6/umd/popper.min.js"
    integrity="sha384-wHAiFfRlMFy6i5SRaxvfOCifBUQy1xHdJ/yoi7FRNXMRBu5WHdZYu1hA6ZOblgut"
    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <script src="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.2.1/js/bootstrap.min.js"
    integrity="sha384-B0UglyR+jN6CkvvICOB2joaf5I4l3gm9GU6Hc1og6Ls7i6U/mkkaduKaBhlAXv9k"
    crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</body>

</html>